String
------
1. String is the special name for character array
2. String is the sequence of characters
3. String is derived datatype
4. String also deals with the concept of indexing, because it also follows number system 
5. Prerequisite for string allocation is base address
6. String also works on continuous memory allocation
7. String elements have same name but differentiable by there indexing
8. String are of two types  : 
    a. fixed length
    b. variable length string 
        i. length controlled string 
        ii. delimited String
9. End of string is represented by Null Character (delimiter) '\0'
10. Here we use %s format specifier

    0     1     2     3     4     5
    H     E     L     L     O     \0
  ch[0] ch[1] ch[2] ch[3] ch[4] ch[5]
  1000  1001  1002  1003  1004  1005   